f(a) = r \cos(a) - m \sin(a)
\sqrt{r^2+m^2}
f(a) = r \cos(a) - m \sin(a) = \sqrt{r^2+m^2}(\frac{r}{\sqrt{r^2+m^2}} \cos a - \frac{m}{\sqrt{r^2+m^2}} \cos a)
\cos \theta = \frac{r}{\sqrt{r^2+m^2}}
\sin \theta = \frac{m}{\sqrt{r^2+m^2}}
f(a) = \sqrt{r^2+m^2} \cos (a+\theta)
r\cos a - m \sin a= \sqrt{r^2+m^2}\left(\dfrac{r}{\sqrt{r^2+m^2}}\cos a - \dfrac{m}{\sqrt{r^2+m^2}} \sin a\right)
b
\sin b=\dfrac{r}{\sqrt{r^2+m^2}}
\cos b=\dfrac{m}{\sqrt{r^2+m^2}}
\frac{m^2}{r\sqrt{\frac{m^2}{r^2}+1}}+\frac r{\sqrt{\frac{m^2}{r^2}+1}}
=\frac{m^2}{\sqrt{m^2+r^2}}+\frac{r^2}{\sqrt{m^2+r^2}}
=\frac{m^2+r^2}{\sqrt{m^2+r^2}}=\sqrt{m^2+r^2}
